{"questionId":"9066433","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Carbonated water is produced when carbon dioxide is dissolved in water under pressure. The following equilibria are established.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Equilibrium (1) &nbsp;CO<sub>2</sub> (g)&nbsp;<img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/5986/5.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"64\" height=\"25\"> CO<sub>2</sub> (aq)</span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Equilibrium (2) &nbsp;CO<sub>2</sub> (aq) + H<sub>2</sub>O (l) <img src=\"__IMG__/65b0fb4431621b5dac9283da73c2c434e0d98be6.png\" width=\"49\" height=\"14\"> H<sup>+</sup> (aq) + HCO<sub>3</sub><sup>−</sup> (aq)</span></span></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Aqueous sodium hydrogencarbonate has a pH of approximately 7 at 298 K.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Sketch a graph of pH against volume when 25.0cm<sup>3</sup> of 0.100 mol dm<sup>−3</sup> NaOH (aq) is gradually added to 10.0cm<sup>3</sup> of 0.0500 mol dm<sup>−3</sup> NaHCO<sub>3</sub> (aq).</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/adb9191269ebef3cd0b41380d4349c7f9a50c184.png\" width=\"569\" height=\"344\"></span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/f96f80107b3099b439624b54f30121f292e64d19.png\" width=\"579\" height=\"358\"></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">S-shaped curve from ~7 to between 12 and 14 &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">equivalence point at 5 cm<sup>3</sup> &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>Accept starting point &gt;6~7.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9066433","referenceCode":"19M.2.hl.TZ2.f","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Aqueous sodium hydrogencarbonate has a pH of approximately 7 at 298 K. Sketch a graph of pH against volume when 25.0cm3 of 0.100 mol dm−3 NaOH (aq) is gradually added to 10.0cm3 of","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"f","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 18: Acids and bases","18.3 pH curves","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 18: Acids and bases"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}